    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras are positioned for a high-ceiling offensive output today, anchored by **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (80.98), who registers as our top play against Sasaki. Despite his lower slot in the batting order, the matchup against a high-xERA starter (5.52) combined with favorable wind conditions and a robust platoon advantage makes him a mandatory start in the pursuit of SB volume. **Junior Caminero** (71.50) and **Trea Turner** (70.16) also grade out as elite options; **Trea Turner** leverages a prime leadoff spot against a modest Elder, while **Junior Caminero** benefits from a strong SP-skill boost against Ober. **Kyle Schwarber** (66.62) provides our most potent power-threat-to-matchup alignment, with his elite xwOBA effectively neutralizing any minor dynamic platoon concerns.\n\nOn the bench, **Victor Scott II** (38.48) was the most difficult exclusion. While his speed profile usually makes him a priority, the combination of a tough matchup against Woo (3.30 xERA) and an unfavorable #9 hole in the lineup dropped his efficiency score below our 40.0 floor. We are opting to sacrifice the marginal SB upside to protect our game cap integrity. Elsewhere, we remain cautious regarding **Yordan Alvarez** (59.36); while he remains a \"strong\" start, his efficiency is slightly hampered by a L/L platoon disadvantage against Weathers. Additionally, managers should note that **Christian Yelich** remains sidelined, and **Carson Benge** is unavailable due to a confirmed rainout, further narrowing our options for substitution should the early innings turn against us.",
